  <description type="morphology">Herbs, perennial. Stems: basal produced; flowering erect, 25–40 cm, sparsely sericeous. Leaves of flowering stems opposite to subopposite; blade linear-lanceolate to narrowly oblanceolate, 10–20 × 1–1.5 mm, apex acute, &lt;usually indurate&gt;, abaxial surface sparsely pilose on midvein and margins, adaxial glabrous. Pedicels 1 per axil, 1–2 mm. Flowers: calyx 1.8–2 mm, &lt;indurate, shiny, yellow-brown basally in fruit&gt;, outer sepals shorter than or equaling inner. Capsules ellipsoid to ovoid, 1.5–2 × 1–1.2 mm, ± equaling to slightly longer than calyx. Seeds (1–)2(–3).</description>
